No offense, but this isn&#039;t a very good solution... 

/**
   * @property isEnabled
   * @type {boolean}
   * @default false
   * @protected
   */
  public isEnabled:boolean = false;

The great thing about JSDoc for JavaScript is that it can take standard-looking, minimal comments and generate relatively useful documentation. If you have to basically rewrite every declaration into your doc comments, then you either can&#039;t use refactoring tools or have to deal with the fact that your documentation is going to get out of date fast.
